HEADWORD: Eyot
<hw>Ey"ot</hw> <pr>(⟦imac⟧"⟦ocr⟧t <it>or</it> ⟦amac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ey</ets> (AS. <ets>⟦imac⟧g</ets> or Icel.
<ets>ey</ets>) + F. dim. termination <ets>-ot</ets>; cf. AS.
<ets>⟦imac⟧geo⟦edh⟧</ets>. See <er>Island</er>, and cf.
<er>Ait</er>.]</ety> <def>A little island in a river or lake. See
<er>Ait</er>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>ait</asp>, <asp>ayt</asp>,
<asp>ey</asp>, <asp>eyet</asp>, and <asp>eyght</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
